39 and their families; and
40 WHEREAS, Valerie's efforts have made a significant impact on improving the lives of
41 cancer patients and will continue to be felt for years to come as her story and advocacy lead
42 to meaningful policy changes and inspire others to stand up for those in need.
43 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE that the members of this body
44 commend Valerie Taylor for her outstanding contributions to the Leukemia & Lymphoma
45 Society and to the broader cancer community, recognizing her as a fierce advocate, a
46 survivor, and a hero who has made a lasting impact in the fight for better healthcare access
47 and treatments for blood cancer patients in Georgia and across the country.
